name: Greek Mountain
descriptionShort: Tisane, Greek Mountain flowers, lemon, spice
descriptionFull: From the slopes of the Taygetos Mountains to your teacup, this traditional Mediterranean tisane possesses an herbaceous hint of lemon. Long valued by Greek mothers for its ability to soothe the stresses of the day.

name: Rooibush Jungle Fire
descriptionShort: Zanzibar cloves, cinnamon oil, orange and lemon oils
descriptionFull: Clove and cinnamon sparkle alongside the natural sweetness of Rooibush, A satisfying, spicy heat.

name: Gourmet Herbal Tea
descriptionShort: Lemon grass, lemon myrtle, Moldavian dragonhead, elderberry blossoms and vanilla bean pieces
descriptionFull: Light-colored in the cup, sweet and vanilla flavored with a touch of lemony freshness.

name: Asian Pear
descriptionShort: Green tea from India, Japan and China, orange blossoms and flavor
descriptionFull: Crisp Asian Pear with a subtle yet enduring flavor and mild fragrance. Green teas from India, Japan and Ceylon, orange blossoms, and natural flavor.

name: Mogli Chai
descriptionShort: Cinnamon, cardamom, ginger, cloves and pepper.
descriptionFull: This herbal Chai blend has all the spice but leaves behind the tea for a naturally caffeine free treat. Brilliant with a touch of sugar and milk.

name: Hibiscus Blossom
descriptionFull: Tart and sweet, the infusion of these crimson flower blossoms is adored around the world.

name: Grandpa Harmsen
descriptionShort: Coriander, fennel, ginger, licorice root, anise, cinnamon, lemon balm, peppermint leaves and cornflower blossoms
descriptionFull: Coriander, licorice and cinnamon satisfy in this sweet and spicy herbal blend.

name: China Fancy White Peony
descriptionShort: Notes of chestnut, honey and white flowers
descriptionFull: An inspiring "New Style" Chinese White tea hailing from Fuding county in Fuijan Province. Created by a fine plucking of the bud and first two leaves in late March or early April, first grade Pai Mu Tan (or White Peony) is distinguished by its high count of silver downy buds. A pale blonde infusion reveals the slightest astringency with clean notes of chestnut, honey and white flowers.

name: Country Peach Passion
descriptionFull: Juicy peach flavor and floral chamomile.

name: Perfect Peach
descriptionFull: Like freshly baked peach pie but in a teacup

name: Smooth Strawberry Dream
descriptionShort: Honeybush tea from Africa, caramel bits, flavor, strawberry pieces and strawberry leaves, milk and soybeans
descriptionFull: Discover new depths of sweetness. Caramel and strawberry swirl effortlessly with South African Honeybush for a guilt and caffeine free dessert blend.

name: English Westminster
descriptionFull: More stiff and brisk than our English Breakfast - owing to the absence of Darjeeling tea - the Westminster has been known to persuade many a tea lover to renounce their customary teabag blend.

name: Jasmine Pearls
descriptionFull: Scented with jasmine blossoms, these Chinese green tea leaves are shaped into beautiful hand-rolled pearls of tea. During infusion the pearls unfurl releasing their delicate scent and soft floral flavor.

name: Lemon Zinger
descriptionFull: Blend of real lemons and lemongrass with hibiscus, the vibrant tropical flower that gives all Zinger teas their signature tangy taste and ruby-red color. A bright tea perfect in any weather.

name: Chamomile
descriptionFull: Soothing aroma and subtle sweet apple flavor. Blended with the finest chamomile flowers from around the world to create a relaxing cup for any time of day.
